# UI Package

`package ui` provides theme constants, layout constants, and reusable stateless widgets.

## Theme (`theme.odin`)

All colors are compile-time `rl.Color` constants (Catppuccin Mocha palette). When adding new theme colors, follow the existing pattern:

```
NAME :: rl.Color{r, g, b, 255}
```

Never hardcode color literals in widget or draw code — always reference a theme constant.

## Layout (`layout.odin`)

All layout values are compile-time `i32` constants derived from a small set of base values (`WINDOW_W`, `MARGIN`, `PICKER_SIZE`). Derived constants should reference their parents, not magic numbers.

## Widgets (`widgets.odin`)

Widgets are immediate-mode: they draw themselves AND return interaction results in the same call. Follow the pattern:

```odin
draw_button :: proc(rect: rl.Rectangle, label: cstring, mouse: rl.Vector2, ...) -> (clicked: bool, hovering: bool)
```

- Accept `mouse: rl.Vector2` — widgets check their own hover/click state
- Accept `rl.Rectangle` for positioning — the caller decides layout
- Return named values for interaction feedback
- Use `rl.DrawRectangleRounded` with roundness `0.3` and segments `6` for consistent look
- May import `"../color"` for color helpers only — never import `"../data"`

## Wheel (`wheel.odin`)

Image-generation procedures (`rebuild_sv`, `rebuild_wheel`, `wheel_pick`) operate on `^rl.Image` and are called when the hue, value, or picker size changes. They write pixels directly via pointer arithmetic.
